cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language generation and machine learning techniques to generate textual descriptions of entities in a knowledge graph. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural network models, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with entity classification and information retrieval, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) respectively. Finally, the paper uses dynamic memory-based networks, which are a type of recurrent neural network, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
